cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of single image super-resolution, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning a mixture of deep networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks as the SR inference module also suggests the possibility of incorporating techniques from neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents extensive experiments to evaluate the performance of the proposed method, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
